docs.text: for the uninitiated , newcomers aaron eckhart and matt malloy play chad and howard , two corporate drones who are dispatched by their nameless company to a remote branch office for a six week assignment .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: chad and howard are archetypes , examples of which you can no doubt find in your own place of business .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: chad is the blond golden boy , genetically engineered for success , the natural charmer who seems to glide effortlessly up the corporate ladder .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: howard is chad's boss , but he is weaker of will , the clumsy practitioner of office politics who has achieved his position through dogged persistence rather than raw talent .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: we first meet them awaiting their flight in a drab airport lounge .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there chad suggests a scheme worthy of a shakespearean villain : he and howard will find a vulnerable single woman at the branch office , woo her simultaneously , win her love , and then dump her .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the reason ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: both men have recently been dumped themselves , and chad sees an easy route to revenge against the fairer sex .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: " it'll restore a little dignity to our lives , " he says .

docs.text: howard , helpless against the force of chad's will , agrees to the plan .

docs.text: they quickly spot their prey in the form of christine ( stacy edwards ) , a fragile deaf woman working as a temp .

docs.text: chad moves in for the kill , flashing his golden boy smile , plying christine with lunch , then flowers , then dinner .

docs.text: soon a tragic lovers' triangle develops : christine loves chad , chad loves himself , and howard loves christine on the grounds that , since she's handicapped and shy , she just might be wretched and lonely enough to settle for him .

docs.text: in chad , writer/director labute and actor eckhart have created one of the most chilling monsters ever committed to film-hannibal lector may eat human flesh , but chad is an eater of souls .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his evil is as subtle as a viper's , and as easy as his smile .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: we watch in stunned disbelief as he back-stabs coworkers , humiliates his subordinates , and works his deadly venom into christine's heart .

docs.text: his character would be a joke if he wasn't so chillingly real- all of us have worked with a chad , and some of us may be him .

docs.text: he's the guy who takes your job and then laughs at you for your weakness .

docs.text: maybe it's just the english major in me , but chad , in his motiveless cruelty towards christine and his careful manipulation of howard , can be seen as a symbol of unbridled capitalism , of greed without conscience .
